{"questionId":"9746","questionHtml":"<p>In a coffee shop, the time it takes to serve a customer can be modelled by a normal distribution&nbsp;with a mean of 1.5 minutes and a standard deviation of 0.4 minutes.</p>\n<p>Two customers enter the shop together. They are served one at a time.</p>\n<p>Find the probability that the total time taken to serve both customers will be less than 4 minutes.</p>\n<p>Clearly state any assumptions you have made.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>let <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"T\">\n  <mi>T</mi>\n</math></span> be the time to serve both customers and&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{T_i}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msub>\n      <mi>T</mi>\n      <mi>i</mi>\n    </msub>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> the time to serve the <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"i\">\n  <mi>i</mi>\n</math></span>th customer</p>\n<p>assuming independence of&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{T_1}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msub>\n      <mi>T</mi>\n      <mn>1</mn>\n    </msub>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> and&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{T_2}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msub>\n      <mi>T</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msub>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>R1</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"T\">\n  <mi>T</mi>\n</math></span>&nbsp;is normally distributed and&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"T = {T_1} + {T_2}\">\n  <mi>T</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <msub>\n      <mi>T</mi>\n      <mn>1</mn>\n    </msub>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <msub>\n      <mi>T</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msub>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>&nbsp;(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"E\\left( T \\right) = 1.5 + 1.5 = 3\">\n  <mi>E</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>T</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>1.5</mn>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>1.5</mn>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>3</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{\\text{Var}}\\left( T \\right) = {0.4^2} + {0.4^2} = 0.32\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>Var</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mi>T</mi>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mn>0.4</mn>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mn>0.4</mn>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>0.32</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>M1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"P\\left( {T < 4} \\right) = 0.961\">\n  <mi>P</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>T</mi>\n      <mo>&lt;</mo>\n      <mn>4</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>0.961</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[6 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9746","referenceCode":"SPM.1.AHL.TZ0.10","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"In a coffee shop, the time it takes to serve a customer can be modelled by a normal distribution with a mean of 1.5 minutes and a standard deviation of 0.4 minutes. Two customers e","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"10","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 6]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","AHL 4.15—Central limit theorem"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}